## Avatar

![][image1]

### **1\. General Information**

| Component name: | Avatar |
| :---- | :---- |
| Category: | **Display & Feedback Components** |
| Description: | **The Avatar component serves as a visual representation of users or entities in a digital interface. It enhances user recognition and personalizes the user experience, playing a vital role in social interactions within digital platforms.** |

### **2\. Usage Guidelines**

| It should be used when: | Use an Avatar when you want to visually represent a user or identity—such as a profile picture, user initials, or a brand logo. It helps users quickly recognize and associate the identity with the related content. |
| :---- | :---- |
| Should not be used when: | Avoid using Avatars when the content isn’t related to a person or identifiable entity. Also, skip it in contexts where visual identity isn’t relevant—like purely numerical data or transactional lists. |
| Good guidelines for design (Best Practices): |  |
| ✅Correct approach: | Avatars should be shown as circles or rounded squares, using high-quality images when available. Use initials as a fallback when no image is present. Size should match the context—smaller in lists, larger in profile views. |
| ❌Guidelines to avoid: | Avoid blurry or poorly cropped images. Don’t use Avatars redundantly or in places where they don’t enhance understanding. Also, don’t neglect to show a proper fallback (like initials) when an image is missing. |

| illustration: |  |
| ----- | :---- |
| Example of Best Practices: |  |
| ![][image8] **Picture Avatar** |  |
| Description | Displays a personal photograph or chosen image of the user. |
| Use Cases | It is ideal for Profiles, professional networks, and any platform where individual identity is critical. Design Guidelines Ensure high-resolution images for clarity. Provide user guidance for uploading images, including recommended dimensions and file size limits. |
| ![][image9] **Alphabet Avatar** |  |
| Description | Shows one or more initials from the user's name, typically used when a personal image is unavailable. |
| Use Cases | It is useful in business applications like email clients, collaboration tools, or other places where users have not set a custom picture. Design Guidelines: Select a legible font, ensuring readability at small sizes. Use contrasting background colors to enhance visibility.	 |
| ![][image10]**Icon Avatar** |  |
| Description | Utilizes AXONS symbols. |
| Use Cases | It is best suited for scenarios where personal identity is not required or should remain anonymous, like specific forums or feedback tools. Design Guidelines: Choose simple, universally recognizable icons or AXONS systems. Offer a variety of icons to cater to different user preferences. |
